' @id(SEQ-AGENT-PREPARE)
' @ref(USE-AGENT-PREPARE)
' @desc(SEQ-AGENT-PREPARE, "Runtime flow of `mdd agent --kind <agent>`: the Commands::Agent arm in mdd-cli parses the kind via AgentKind::parse, discovers the Project, and calls mdd_agent::prepare_agent. prepare_agent writes the per-agent instruction file under .mdd/docs and then runs each .mdd/hooks/pre-code* executable in sorted order, bailing on the first non-zero exit. It returns an AgentPreparationReport { instruction_file, hooks_run } the CLI prints. mdd-agent becomes a real mdd-cli dependency.")
title MDD agent prepare — runtime flow (objective)

actor "Developer / Agent" as Dev <<missing>>
participant "mdd agent --kind\n(mdd-cli)" as Cli
participant "prepare_agent\n(mdd-agent)" as Agent
participant "filesystem\n.mdd/docs + .mdd/hooks" as Fs

Dev -> Cli : mdd agent --kind claude
Cli -> Cli : AgentKind::parse("claude")
Cli -> Agent : prepare_agent(&project, kind)
Agent -> Fs : write .mdd/docs/claude-mdd.md
Agent -> Fs : run .mdd/hooks/pre-code* (sorted)
Agent --> Cli : AgentPreparationReport
Cli --> Dev : print instruction_file + hooks_run
@enduml
